data.description: PRICE DROP JUST IN TIME FOR THE HOLIDAYS!   Welcome to 3013 Keswick RD an oasis located in Hampden Historic District.    Boasting 1344 square feet of unique original features including hardwood floors throughout and exposed brick on two levels. The upper level includes a spacious layout with 2 generously sized bedrooms, 1 oversized luxury bathroom with dual sinks, and upstairs laundry in the master bedroom.  The open space main level has a half bath, modern kitchen with beautiful cabinetry, spacious separate dining room for formal dining table and chairs.  The backyard has generous green space and a deck and backs to Wyman park.  This home is within walking, biking, or a short drive's distance from  Stony Run, the Gwynns Falls Trail, Druid Hill Park, the Rotunda, Remington, the Avenue, Hopkins, R. House, Charles Village, the 32nd Street Farmers Market, MOM's Organic Market, to name a few of the ever-expanding list of entertainment, parks, restaurants and cafes.  The water heater is brand new; and the two additional air conditioning in each bedroom can convey.
